zhoneIpSLA.name: zhoneIpSLA

revisions.description: Simplified most leaf names, removing the zhoneIpSLM prefix. Changed some leaf names to clarify their purpose. Modified the markup, correcting the Zhone provisioning model for this feature. Referencing ifIndex made little sense within this feature as IP is tied more to the management database and route domain. Traps have been modified to reference the source IP address for the connection, allowing administrators to track the location of the device originating the static path configuration.

zhoneIpSLA.description: This is the MIB Module for IPSLA Feature Configuration and reporting.

zhoneIpSLAGlobalEnable.name: zhoneIpSLAGlobalEnable
zhoneIpSLAGlobalEnable.description: This object specifies whether to enable feature actions.

zhoneIpSLAGlobalPollInterval.name: zhoneIpSLAGlobalPollInterval
zhoneIpSLAGlobalPollInterval.description: This object specifies the time interval in seconds between the inband IPSLA communications among IPSLA devices.

zhoneIpSLACosActionTable.name: zhoneIpSLACosActionTable
zhoneIpSLACosActionTable.description: This table has the Service Level Agreement (SLA) CoS action configuration options.

zhoneIpSLACosActionEntry.name: zhoneIpSLACosActionEntry
zhoneIpSLACosActionEntry.description: An entry in the IPSLA Action By CoS Configuration Table.

zhoneIpSLACosActionIndex.name: zhoneIpSLACosActionIndex
zhoneIpSLACosActionIndex.description: There are 8 entries present for each device. actionIndex values 1 to 8 correspond exactly to Class Of Service (CoS) indices 0 to 7.

zhoneIpSLACosActionName.name: zhoneIpSLACosActionName
zhoneIpSLACosActionName.description: The ascii name of the SLA CoS action entry, up to 9 characters in length. Blank names are not allowed.

zhoneIpSLACosActionTrapOnError.name: zhoneIpSLACosActionTrapOnError
zhoneIpSLACosActionTrapOnError.description: Specifies whether a trap is issued when any SLA performance error threshold within this CoS is crossed.

zhoneIpSLACosActionTimeoutErrThresh.name: zhoneIpSLACosActionTimeoutErrThresh
zhoneIpSLACosActionTimeoutErrThresh.description: Specifies the number of consecutive missed IP SLA responses within this CoS before a zhoneIpSLATimeoutTrap is issued.

zhoneIpSLACosActionTimeoutClrThresh.name: zhoneIpSLACosActionTimeoutClrThresh
zhoneIpSLACosActionTimeoutClrThresh.description: Specifies the number of consecutive IPSLA responses within this CoS which must be received before the timeout error condition is cleared.

zhoneIpSLACosActionLatencyErrThresh.name: zhoneIpSLACosActionLatencyErrThresh
zhoneIpSLACosActionLatencyErrThresh.description: Specifies the 15 sample average roundtrip latency value which must be exceeded within this CoS before a zhoneIpSLALatencyTrap is issued. The value is specified in milliseconds.

zhoneIpSLACosActionLatencyClrThresh.name: zhoneIpSLACosActionLatencyClrThresh
zhoneIpSLACosActionLatencyClrThresh.description: Specifies the number of consecutive IPSLA latency samples for which the 15 sample average roundtrip latency must be below the configured SLA latency error threshold within this CoS before the latency error condition is cleared.

zhoneIpSLACosActionJitterErrThresh.name: zhoneIpSLACosActionJitterErrThresh
zhoneIpSLACosActionJitterErrThresh.description: Specifies the 15 sample roundtrip jitter value which must be exceeded within this CoS before a zhoneIpSLAJitterTrap is issued. The value is specified in milliseconds.

zhoneIpSLACosActionJitterClrThresh.name: zhoneIpSLACosActionJitterClrThresh
zhoneIpSLACosActionJitterClrThresh.description: Specifies the number of consecutive IPSLA RTT samples for which the 15 sample roundtrip jitter must be below the configured SLA jitter error threshold within this CoS before the jitter error condition is cleared.

zhoneIpSLACosActionMetrics.name: zhoneIpSLACosActionMetrics
zhoneIpSLACosActionMetrics.description: Specifies if Latency and Availability meaurements should be carried out for this CoS. The default is enabled(1).

zhoneIpSLACosActionPacketSize.name: zhoneIpSLACosActionPacketSize
zhoneIpSLACosActionPacketSize.description: Specifies the minimum IPSLA Ping packet size in bytes. The range is 64 thru 2048 if the target IP device is running IPSLA, 64 thru 512 otherwise.

zhoneIpSLACosMapTable.name: zhoneIpSLACosMapTable
zhoneIpSLACosMapTable.description: This table contains the Service Level Management DSCP-to-CoS mapping.

zhoneIpSLACosMapEntry.name: zhoneIpSLACosMapEntry
zhoneIpSLACosMapEntry.description: An entry in the IPSLA COS Map Table.

zhoneIpSLACosMapDscpIndex.name: zhoneIpSLACosMapDscpIndex
zhoneIpSLACosMapDscpIndex.description: There are 64 entries present each representing a DIFFSRV code point (0 thru 63, bits 000000 thru 111111), for each device. dscpIndex values 1 to 64 correspond exactly to DIFFSRV codepoint values 0 to 63.

zhoneIpSLACosMapCosActionIndex.name: zhoneIpSLACosMapCosActionIndex
zhoneIpSLACosMapCosActionIndex.description: This object is a pointer to the entry in zhoneIpSLACosActionTable. Value 0 indicates that no CoS action is assigned. The map entries recommended in rfc 2597 are present by default.

zhoneIpSLAStaticPathTable.name: zhoneIpSLAStaticPathTable
zhoneIpSLAStaticPathTable.description: This table has the list of static Path IP Addresses

zhoneIpSLAStaticPathEntry.name: zhoneIpSLAStaticPathEntry
zhoneIpSLAStaticPathEntry.description: An entry in the IPSLA Configuration Table.

zhoneIpSLAStaticPathRdIndex.name: zhoneIpSLAStaticPathRdIndex
zhoneIpSLAStaticPathRdIndex.description: Route Domain Index of the target IP address.

zhoneIpSLAStaticPathTargetIP.name: zhoneIpSLAStaticPathTargetIP
zhoneIpSLAStaticPathTargetIP.description: Specifies the IP Address of the device which is at the other end of the path.

zhoneIpSLAStaticPathForwarding.name: zhoneIpSLAStaticPathForwarding
zhoneIpSLAStaticPathForwarding.description: If enabled, all native static IP path entities will include this IP in IPSLA ping messages as a forwarded IP, resulting in remote IPSLA devices' inclusion of this IP as a dynamic IPSLA initiator. Remote IPSLA devices will then act as a proxy for the local IPSLA device in sending out IPSLA pings. Forwarded IPs are NOT propagated past the first remote IPSLA device. Received forwarded IPs are dynamic entries which get aged out unless IPSLA protocol messages are received which contain their IP as a forwarded IP. The agetime is a multiple of the proxying device's global poll-secs (object zhoneIpSLAGlobalPollInterval), based upon a certain maximum of forwarded paths per device and the number of path forwarding messages allowed within the minimum 64-byte IPSLA Ping packet. Valid values are enabled(1), disabled(2).

zhoneIpSLAStaticPathState.name: zhoneIpSLAStaticPathState
zhoneIpSLAStaticPathState.description: Specifies if the IPSLA feature actions will be exerted on the current member of the static entry list. This leaf allows the user to toggle the feature per static path without deleting the current static path configuration. Valid values are enabled(1), disabled(2).

zhoneIpSLAStaticPathRowstatus.name: zhoneIpSLAStaticPathRowstatus
zhoneIpSLAStaticPathRowstatus.description: This object is used to create new rows in this table, modify existing rows, and to delete existing rows.

zhoneIpSLAPathConnectTable.name: zhoneIpSLAPathConnectTable
zhoneIpSLAPathConnectTable.description: IP Path table for reporting connection statistics.

zhoneIpSLAPathConnectEndpointIP.name: zhoneIpSLAPathConnectEndpointIP
zhoneIpSLAPathConnectEndpointIP.description: Specifies the IP Address of the target device which is at the other end of the path.

zhoneIpSLAPathConnectDevName.name: zhoneIpSLAPathConnectDevName
zhoneIpSLAPathConnectDevName.description: Specifies the name of the remote device.

zhoneIpSLAPathConnectDevType.name: zhoneIpSLAPathConnectDevType
zhoneIpSLAPathConnectDevType.description: Specifies the type of the remote device.

zhoneIpSLAPathConnectStatus.name: zhoneIpSLAPathConnectStatus
zhoneIpSLAPathConnectStatus.description: Specifies the availability status of the remote.

zhoneIpSLAPathConnectSrcIP.name: zhoneIpSLAPathConnectSrcIP
zhoneIpSLAPathConnectSrcIP.description: The object specifies the source discovery Ip Address.

zhoneIpSLAPathConnectDiscoveryType.name: zhoneIpSLAPathConnectDiscoveryType
zhoneIpSLAPathConnectDiscoveryType.description: The object specifies the source discovery type.

zhoneIpSLAPathConnectUpTime.name: zhoneIpSLAPathConnectUpTime
zhoneIpSLAPathConnectUpTime.description: The object specifies the amount of time in seconds that elapsed since the last transition from Inactive to Active.

zhoneIpSLAPathConnectPollType.name: zhoneIpSLAPathConnectPollType
zhoneIpSLAPathConnectPollType.description: The object specifies the role played by the local device in collection of latency and availability statistics. Initiator(1) - this is the unit that initiates the IPSLA ping packet used for statistics collection; Responder(2) - this is the unit that returns the IPSLA ping packet sent by the Initiator.

zhoneIpSLAPathConnectCosMismatch.name: zhoneIpSLAPathConnectCosMismatch
zhoneIpSLAPathConnectCosMismatch.description: The object specifies the number of IPSLA ping packets received which indicate a mismatch between the Class Of Service definitions at the remote unit with those of the local unit.

zhoneIpSLAPathConnectLastCosActionIndex.name: zhoneIpSLAPathConnectLastCosActionIndex
zhoneIpSLAPathConnectLastCosActionIndex.description: The object specifies the COS action Id used within the most recently transmitted IPSLA ping on this connection.

zhoneIpSLAPathStatByCOSTable.name: zhoneIpSLAPathStatByCOSTable
zhoneIpSLAPathStatByCOSTable.description: IP Path Table for reporting round-trip-time stats and dropped responses.

zhoneIpSLAPathStatByCOSEntry.name: zhoneIpSLAPathStatByCOSEntry
zhoneIpSLAPathStatByCOSEntry.description: An entry in the IP Path Statistics By COS Table.

zhoneIpSLAPathStatByCOSTargetIP.name: zhoneIpSLAPathStatByCOSTargetIP
zhoneIpSLAPathStatByCOSTargetIP.description: Specifies the IP Address of the device which is at the other end of the path.

zhoneIpSLAPathStatByCOSStatus.name: zhoneIpSLAPathStatByCOSStatus
zhoneIpSLAPathStatByCOSStatus.description: Specifies the status of the Cos. Writing to this leaf will cause objects zhoneIpSLAPathStatByCOSLastRTT, zhoneIpSLAPathStatByCOSMinRTT, zhoneIpSLAPathStatByCOSAvgRTT, zhoneIpSLAPathStatByCOSMaxRTT, and zhoneIpSLAPathStatByCOSDropResp to be cleared.

zhoneIpSLAPathStatByCOSLastRTT.name: zhoneIpSLAPathStatByCOSLastRTT
zhoneIpSLAPathStatByCOSLastRTT.description: The object specifies the latest round trip latency in milliseconds between this unit and the unit at the far end of the IP Enabled circuit.

zhoneIpSLAPathStatByCOSMinRTT.name: zhoneIpSLAPathStatByCOSMinRTT
zhoneIpSLAPathStatByCOSMinRTT.description: The object specifies the minimum round trip latency in milliseconds between this unit and the unit at the far end of the IP Enabled circuit. This is the least value of the last 15 ping trials.

zhoneIpSLAPathStatByCOSAvgRTT.name: zhoneIpSLAPathStatByCOSAvgRTT
zhoneIpSLAPathStatByCOSAvgRTT.description: The object specifies the average round trip latency in milliseconds between this unit and the unit at the far end of the IP Enabled circuit. This is the average value over the last 15 ping trials.

zhoneIpSLAPathStatByCOSMaxRTT.name: zhoneIpSLAPathStatByCOSMaxRTT
zhoneIpSLAPathStatByCOSMaxRTT.description: The object specifies the maximum round trip latency in milliseconds between this unit and the unit at the far end of the IP Enabled circuit. This is the greatest value of the last 15 ping trials.

zhoneIpSLAPathStatByCOSDroppedResp.name: zhoneIpSLAPathStatByCOSDroppedResp
zhoneIpSLAPathStatByCOSDroppedResp.description: The object specifies the number of IPSLA pings for which a response was not received from the far end device.

zhoneIpSLAPathStatByIntervalTable.name: zhoneIpSLAPathStatByIntervalTable
zhoneIpSLAPathStatByIntervalTable.description: IP Path Table for reporting round-trip-time stats and dropped responses. This table's top index represents one of 96 slices of data taken at 15 minute intervals, allowing the user to track performance over a 24 hour period.

zhoneIpSLAPathStatByIntervalEntry.name: zhoneIpSLAPathStatByIntervalEntry
zhoneIpSLAPathStatByIntervalEntry.description: An entry in the IP Path Statistics By Interval and COS Table.

zhoneIpSLAPathStatByIntervalIndex.name: zhoneIpSLAPathStatByIntervalIndex
zhoneIpSLAPathStatByIntervalIndex.description: Specifies which of the 96 15-minute interval data slices to report.

zhoneIpSLAPathStatByIntervalTargetIP.name: zhoneIpSLAPathStatByIntervalTargetIP
zhoneIpSLAPathStatByIntervalTargetIP.description: Specifies the IP Address of the device which is at the other end of the path.

zhoneIpSLAPathStatByIntervalDateTime.name: zhoneIpSLAPathStatByIntervalDateTime
zhoneIpSLAPathStatByIntervalDateTime.description: Describes the date and time the current interval data slice was stored.

zhoneIpSLAPathStatByIntervalStatus.name: zhoneIpSLAPathStatByIntervalStatus
zhoneIpSLAPathStatByIntervalStatus.description: Specifies the status of the Cos.

zhoneIpSLAPathStatByIntervalMinRTT.name: zhoneIpSLAPathStatByIntervalMinRTT
zhoneIpSLAPathStatByIntervalMinRTT.description: The object specifies the minimum round trip latency in milliseconds between this unit and the unit at the far end of the IP Enabled circuit. This is the least value of the last 15 ping trials.

zhoneIpSLAPathStatByIntervalAvgRTT.name: zhoneIpSLAPathStatByIntervalAvgRTT
zhoneIpSLAPathStatByIntervalAvgRTT.description: The object specifies the average round trip latency in milliseconds between this unit and the unit at the far end of the IP Enabled circuit. This is the average value over the last 15 ping trials.

zhoneIpSLAPathStatByIntervalMaxRTT.name: zhoneIpSLAPathStatByIntervalMaxRTT
zhoneIpSLAPathStatByIntervalMaxRTT.description: The object specifies the maximum round trip latency in milliseconds between this unit and the unit at the far end of the IP Enabled circuit. This is the greatest value of the last 15 ping trials.

zhoneIpSLAPathStatByIntervalDroppedResp.name: zhoneIpSLAPathStatByIntervalDroppedResp
zhoneIpSLAPathStatByIntervalDroppedResp.description: The object specifies the number of IPSLA pings for which a response was not received from the far end device.

zhoneIpSLATrapsPrefix.name: zhoneIpSLATrapsPrefix
zhoneIpSLATrapsPrefix.description: Prefix 0 for Zhone IPSLA MIB traps as required by SNMPv2

zhoneIpSLATimeoutTrap.name: zhoneIpSLATimeoutTrap
zhoneIpSLATimeoutTrap.description: This trap is generated whenever zhoneIpSLAPathStatByCOSDropResp exceeds zhoneIpSLACosActionTimeoutErrThresh.

zhoneIpSLALatencyTrap.name: zhoneIpSLALatencyTrap
zhoneIpSLALatencyTrap.description: This trap is generated whenever zhoneIpSLAPathStatByCOSAvgRTT exceeds zhoneIpSLACosActionLatencyErrThresh.

zhoneIpSLAJitterTrap.name: zhoneIpSLAJitterTrap
zhoneIpSLAJitterTrap.description: This trap is generated whenever (zhoneIpSLAPathStatByCOSMaxRTT - zhoneIpSLAPathStatByCOSMinRTT) exceeds zhoneIpSLACosActionJitterErrThresh.

zhoneIpSLATimeoutClearTrap.name: zhoneIpSLATimeoutClearTrap
zhoneIpSLATimeoutClearTrap.description: This trap is generated to clear a timeout threshold violation condition.

zhoneIpSLALatencyClearTrap.name: zhoneIpSLALatencyClearTrap
zhoneIpSLALatencyClearTrap.description: This trap is generated to clear a latency threshold violation condition.

zhoneIpSLAJitterClearTrap.name: zhoneIpSLAJitterClearTrap
zhoneIpSLAJitterClearTrap.description: This trap is generated to clear a jitter threshold violation condition.

zhoneIpSLAGlobalsGroup.name: zhoneIpSLAGlobalsGroup
zhoneIpSLAGlobalsGroup.description: The objects determining overall IPSLA behavior.

zhoneIpSLACosActionGroup.name: zhoneIpSLACosActionGroup
zhoneIpSLACosActionGroup.description: The objects in the IPSLA Cos Action table.

zhoneIpSLACOSMapGroup.name: zhoneIpSLACOSMapGroup
zhoneIpSLACOSMapGroup.description: The objects in the IPSLA COS Map table.

zhoneIpSLAStaticPathGroup.name: zhoneIpSLAStaticPathGroup
zhoneIpSLAStaticPathGroup.description: The objects in the IPSLA Static Path table.

zhoneIpSLAPathConnectGroup.name: zhoneIpSLAPathConnectGroup
zhoneIpSLAPathConnectGroup.description: The objects in the IPSLA Path Connection table.

zhoneIpSLAPathStatByCOSGroup.name: zhoneIpSLAPathStatByCOSGroup
zhoneIpSLAPathStatByCOSGroup.description: The objects in the IPSLA Path Stats By COS table.

zhoneIpSLAPathStatByIntervalGroup.name: zhoneIpSLAPathStatByIntervalGroup
zhoneIpSLAPathStatByIntervalGroup.description: The objects in the IPSLA Path Stats By Interval table.

zhoneIpSLACompliance.name: zhoneIpSLACompliance
zhoneIpSLACompliance.description: The compliance statement for SNMP entities which support IPSLA configuration.
